<subSubSection id="F7BA92A9F87EFFB3FF6E3F12FDFBFE50" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="BF1FC122F87EFFB3FF6E3F12FEA9FEC8" blockId="9.[189,303,267,293]" box="[189,303,267,293]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<heading id="E457764EF87EFFB3FF6E3F12FEA9FEC8" bold="true" box="[189,303,267,293]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" reason="3">
<emphasis id="8DD41D30F87EFFB3FF6E3F12FEA9FEC8" bold="true" box="[189,303,267,293]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BF1FC122F87EFFB3FF6E3F20FDFBFE50" blockId="9.[189,1398,313,446]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
This new species is a typical member of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="78A0BAA1F87EFFB3FC5F3F20FB9BFEBE" authorityName="Macfie" authorityYear="1932" box="[908,1053,313,339]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Homobezzia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8DD41D30F87EFFB3FC5F3F20FB9BFEBE" box="[908,1053,313,339]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Homobezzia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It most closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="78A0BAA1F87EFFB3FF6E3F44FEE7FE9A" authorityName="Remm" authorityYear="1967" box="[189,353,349,375]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kuhetiensis">
<emphasis id="8DD41D30F87EFFB3FF6E3F44FEE7FE9A" box="[189,353,349,375]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">B. kuhetiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has similar male genitalia and seminal capsules. However, 
<taxonomicName id="78A0BAA1F87EFFB3FBAD3F44FAA4FE9A" authorityName="Remm" authorityYear="1967" box="[1150,1314,349,375]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kuhetiensis">
<emphasis id="8DD41D30F87EFFB3FBAD3F44FAA4FE9A" box="[1150,1314,349,375]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">B. kuhetiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="78A0BAA1F87EFFB3FF2E3F98FE06FE77" authority="Alwin-Kownacka &amp; Szadziewski &amp; Szwedo, 2017" authorityName="Alwin-Kownacka &amp; Szadziewski &amp; Szwedo" authorityYear="2017" box="[253,384,384,410]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sharjahi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="8DD41D30F87EFFB3FF2E3F98FE89FE77" box="[253,271,385,410]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="8DD41D30F87EFFB3FECD3F99FE06FE77" box="[286,384,384,410]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">sharjahi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="96E7A04BF87EFFB3FE543F99FE64FE77" box="[391,482,384,410]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by its whitish legs with distinct, dark bands, the fore femur has only 2 ventral spines, and the parameres are straight.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
